{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894405479,"sessionID":"ses_2847266b0ffecWMsMka6mCOPeA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8e17850016gUtAJGYHXEhO3","messageID":"msg_d7b8e0409001624Tzs5kTIDUS9","sessionID":"ses_2847266b0ffecWMsMka6mCOPeA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: CLI Invoke and Status Commands (AR-023)\n2: \n3: ## AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status 命令\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n8: | **Language** | Python |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to complete the agent lifecycle management workflow: `pack` → `build` → `publish` → `invoke` → `status`.\n17: \n18: The `invoke` command SHALL:\n19: - Send JSON payloads to deployed agents via HTTP POST requests\n20: - Support custom HTTP headers for authentication and metadata\n21: - Handle both AgentRuntime CR and standard Kubernetes deployments\n22: - Automatically manage session IDs for AgentRuntime invocations\n23: - Parse and display agent responses with proper formatting\n24: \n25: The `status` command SHALL:\n26: - Retrieve and display the current deployment status of agents\n27: - Support both AgentRuntime CR and standard Kubernetes providers\n28: - Present status information in a Rich Table format\n29: - Exit with code 1 when agent is not published or in error state\n30: - Provide clear guidance for next steps based on status\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Scope\n35: \n36: ### In Scope\n37: \n38: 1. **CLI Command Implementation - `invoke`**\n39:    - Add `invoke` subcommand to the Typer CLI application\n40:    - Command options:\n41:      - `workspace` (`-f`, `--workspace`): Path to agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n42:      - `payload` (`--payload`): JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n43:      - `header_list` (`--header`): Custom HTTP headers, repeatable (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token')\n44:      - `provider` (`--provider`): Target provider - 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) [default: \"agentcube\"]\n45:      - `verbose` (`--verbose`): Enable detailed logging\n46: \n47: 2. **CLI Command Implementation - `status`**\n48:    - Add `status` subcommand to the Typer CLI application\n49:    - Command options:\n50:      - `workspace` (`-f`, `--workspace`): Path to agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n51:      - `provider` (`--provider`): Target provider - 'agentcube' or 'k8s' [default: \"agentcube\"]\n52:      - `verbose` (`--verbose`): Enable detailed logging\n53: \n54: 3. **InvokeRuntime Implementation**\n55:    - `InvokeRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n56:    - Core methods:\n57:      - `invoke(workspace_path, payload, headers)`: Main invocation orchestration\n58:      - `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()`: Validate workspace and metadata\n59:      - `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()`: Invoke via AgentRuntime CR\n60:      - `_direct_http_invocation()`: Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments\n61:      - URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR invocations\n62: \n63: 4. **StatusRuntime Implementation**\n64:    - `StatusRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n65:    - Core methods:\n66:      - `get_status(workspace_path, provider)`: Main status retrieval\n67:      - `_get_k8s_status()`: Get status from Kubernetes Deployment\n68:      - `_get_cr_k8s_status()`: Get status from AgentRuntime CR\n69:    - Status value mapping and presentation\n70: \n71: 5. **HTTP Client Integration**\n72:    - Async HTTP client for AgentRuntime invocations\n73:    - Synchronous HTTP client for K8s deployments\n74:    - Session header management (`X-Agentcube-Session-Id`)\n75:    - Payload validation and JSON parsing\n76:    - Header format validation (`key:value`)\n77: \n78: 6. **Error Handling**\n79:    - Invalid JSON payload detection and reporting\n80:    - Invalid header format validation\n81:    - Missing agent_id / not_published state handling\n82:    - HTTP error responses with status codes\n83:    - Timeout handling for invocations\n84:    - Integration with `_handle_error()` for consistent CLI patterns\n85: \n86: ### Out of Scope\n87: \n88: 1. **Agent Development**: Agent business logic implementation\n89: 2. **Persistent Sessions**: Session management beyond single invocation\n90: 3. **Streaming Responses**: Chunked/streaming HTTP response handling\n91: 4. **Load Testing**: Concurrent invocation or performance testing features\n92: 5. **Log Streaming**: Real-time log tailing from agents\n93: 6. **Multi-Agent Orchestration**: Invoking multiple agents in sequence/parallel\n94: 7. **GraphQL Support**: Alternative query language support\n95: 8. **WebSocket Communication**: Persistent connection protocols\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## Design\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 739. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: CLI Invoke and Status Commands (AR-023)\n\n## AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status 命令\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to complete the agent lifecycle management workflow: `pack` → `build` → `publish` → `invoke` → `status`.\n\nThe `invoke` command SHALL:\n- Send JSON payloads to deployed agents via HTTP POST requests\n- Support custom HTTP headers for authentication and metadata","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775894405452,"end":1775894405477}}}}
