{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894443188,"sessionID":"ses_2847266b0ffecWMsMka6mCOPeA","part":{"id":"prt_d7b8eaf610018B6AlgGuAK3uzR","messageID":"msg_d7b8ea3f8001OKP3hoyT3L5000","sessionID":"ses_2847266b0ffecWMsMka6mCOPeA","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":150,"offset":600},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n600: **Approach**: Detect provider automatically from metadata `k8s_deployment.type` without requiring `--provider` flag.\n601: \n602: **Partially Accepted**: Provider flag is kept for explicitness, but default is derived from metadata if available. CLI still accepts explicit override.\n603: \n604: ### Alternative 3: Persistent Session Cache\n605: \n606: **Approach**: Cache session IDs to disk for reuse across CLI invocations.\n607: \n608: **Deferred**: Adds complexity and security concerns. Sessions are managed per-invocation as per current spec. Can be added later if needed.\n609: \n610: ### Alternative 4: Structured Output (JSON)\n611: \n612: **Approach**: Add `--output=json` flag for machine-readable output.\n613: \n614: **Deferred**: Future enhancement. Current implementation focuses on human-readable Rich tables and formatted JSON responses.\n615: \n616: ### Alternative 5: Interactive Invocation Mode\n617: \n618: **Approach**: Support interactive mode for multiple invocations with session reuse.\n619: \n620: **Rejected**: Out of scope for this AR. The CLI follows a one-shot command pattern consistent with other lifecycle commands.\n621: \n622: ---\n623: \n624: ## Verification\n625: \n626: ### Invoke Command Verification\n627: \n628: ```bash\n629: # Prerequisites: pack, build, and publish commands executed\n630: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent\n631: kubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent\n632: kubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s --namespace default\n633: \n634: # Basic invocation with empty payload\n635: echo '{\"message\": \"hello\"}' | kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n636:   --payload '{\"input\": \"test\"}' \\\n637:   --provider k8s\n638: \n639: # Invocation with custom headers\n640: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n641:   --payload '{\"query\": \"status\"}' \\\n642:   --header \"Authorization: Bearer test-token\" \\\n643:   --header \"X-Custom-Header: value\" \\\n644:   --verbose\n645: \n646: # Test invalid JSON payload\n647: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent --payload \"not valid json\" 2>&1 | \\\n648:   grep -q \"Invalid JSON\" && echo \"JSON validation works\"\n649: \n650: # Test invalid header format\n651: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent --header \"no-colon-here\" 2>&1 | \\\n652:   grep -q \"key:value\" && echo \"Header validation works\"\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ### Status Command Verification\n656: \n657: ```bash\n658: # Check status of published agent\n659: kubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s\n660: \n661: # Should display Rich table with status\n662: \n663: # Check status before publish (should exit 1)\n664: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/new-agent --agent-name new-agent\n665: kubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/new-agent 2>&1 | \\\n666:   grep -q \"not published\" && echo \"Not published detection works\"\n667: \n668: # Verify exit code on not_published\n669: kubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/new-agent 2>/dev/null || \\\n670:   [ $? -eq 1 ] && echo \"Exit code 1 on not_published works\"\n671: \n672: # AgentCube provider status\n673: kubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --provider agentcube \\\n674:   --namespace default\n675: kubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider agentcube\n676: ```\n677: \n678: ### Error Handling Verification\n679: \n680: ```bash\n681: # Test missing metadata\n682: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/no-metadata 2>&1 | \\\n683:   grep -q \"metadata\" && echo \"Missing metadata error works\"\n684: \n685: # Test timeout (with slow agent)\n686: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n687:   --payload '{\"sleep\": 60}' \\\n688:   --verbose 2>&1 | grep -q \"timeout\" && echo \"Timeout handling works\"\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ---\n692: \n693: ## References\n694: \n695: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — Detailed CLI design specifications\n696: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Complete requirements specification\n697: - [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) — Python SDK for session management patterns\n698: - [python-sdk/spec.md](python-sdk/spec.md) — SDK HTTP contracts\n699: - [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) — client-go library for AgentRuntime CR\n700: - AR-020 — CLI Pack Command\n701: - AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n702: - AR-022 — CLI Publish Command — Predecessor in lifecycle\n703: \n704: ---\n705: \n706: ## Success Criteria\n707: \n708: ### Invoke Command\n709: \n710: 1. ✅ `invoke` command is registered in Typer CLI with all specified options\n711: 2. ✅ `InvokeRuntime` class implements all required methods per spec\n712: 3. ✅ JSON payload parsing validates input and exits code 1 on invalid JSON\n713: 4. ✅ Header parsing validates `key:value` format and exits code 1 on invalid\n714: 5. ✅ AgentCube provider (`agentcube`) invocations use AgentRuntime URL format\n715: 6. ✅ Session header (`X-Agentcube-Session-Id`) added when metadata contains `session_id`\n716: 7. ✅ K8s provider (`k8s`) uses direct HTTP POST to `agent_endpoint`\n717: 8. ✅ Response is parsed as JSON and displayed formatted\n718: 9. ✅ HTTP errors are caught and displayed with status code\n719: 10. ✅ Missing `agent_id` produces clear \"not published\" error with exit code 1\n720: 11. ✅ All errors use consistent `_handle_error()` pattern\n721: 12. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging and full tracebacks\n722: \n723: ### Status Command\n724: \n725: 1. ✅ `status` command is registered in Typer CLI with all specified options\n726: 2. ✅ `StatusRuntime` class implements all required methods per spec\n727: 3. ✅ AgentCube provider queries AgentRuntime CR status\n728: 4. ✅ K8s provider queries standard K8s Deployment status\n729: 5. ✅ Status displayed in Rich Table format with color coding\n730: 6. ✅ `not_published` status (no `agent_id`) exits with code 1\n731: 7. ✅ `error` or `not_found` status exits with code 1\n732: 8. ✅ `ready` status exits with code 0\n733: 9. ✅ Table includes: status, agent_name, agent_id, provider, namespace, endpoint, replicas\n734: 10. ✅ All errors use consistent `_handle_error()` pattern\n735: 11. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging\n736: \n737: ---\n738: \n739: *AR-023 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 739 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"**Approach**: Detect provider automatically from metadata `k8s_deployment.type` without requiring `--provider` flag.\n\n**Partially Accepted**: Provider flag is kept for explicitness, but default is derived from metadata if available. CLI still accepts explicit override.\n\n### Alternative 3: Persistent Session Cache\n\n**Approach**: Cache session IDs to disk for reuse across CLI invocations.\n\n**Deferred**: Adds complexity and security concerns. Sessions are managed per-invocation as per current spec. Can be added later if needed.\n\n### Alternative 4: Structured Output (JSON)\n\n**Approach**: Add `--output=json` flag for machine-readable output.\n\n**Deferred**: Future enhancement. Current implementation focuses on human-readable Rich tables and formatted JSON responses.\n\n### Alternative 5: Interactive Invocation Mode\n\n**Approach**: Support interactive mode for multiple invocations with session reuse.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775894443180,"end":1775894443186}}}}
